{"body": [{"indent": 0, "text": ["RBD Cluster"], "type": "title", "extent": [117, 133], "level": 0}, {"indent": 0, "type": "summary", "extent": [133, 204], "text": ["Combines fractured pieces or constraints into larger clusters."]}, {"indent": 0, "type": "para", "extent": [204, 529], "text": ["This SOP combines fractured pieces into larger clusters, either by adjusting the ", {"text": ["name"], "type": "code"}, " attribute or by grouping the intracluster and intercluster constraints.\nThe optional incoming ", {"text": ["cluster"], "type": "code"}, " attribute on the constraint geometry points can be further refined with the ", {"text": ["Add Cluster Noise"], "type": "ui"}, " and ", {"text": ["Random Detach"], "type": "ui"}, " parameters."]}, {"body": [{"body": [{"body": [{"indent": 4, "type": "para", "extent": [577, 643], "text": ["Specifies how to apply the clustering to the input geometry."]}, {"body": [{"body": [{"indent": 8, "type": "para", "extent": [663, 880], "text": ["Adjusts the ", {"text": ["name"], "type": "code"}, " primitive attribute to combine pieces into clusters.\n        This will result in fewer objects in the simulation.\n        The constraint geometry is also updated to reflect the new pieces."]}], "indent": 4, "text": ["Combine Pieces"], "extent": [643, 663], "container": true, "type": "dt"}, {"body": [{"indent": 8, "type": "para", "extent": [903, 1405], "text": ["The input geometry is not modified, but primitive groups are added to the constraint geometry to identify constraints between clusters, internal constraints in a cluster, etc.\n        This can be used with the ", {"text": ["RBD Constraint Properties SOP"], "fullpath": "/nodes/sop/rbdconstraintproperties", "scheme": "Node", "type": "link", "value": "/nodes/sop/rbdconstraintproperties"}, " to, for example, create stronger constraints between pieces in the same cluster.\n        With this approach, the clustered chunks may be broken apart during the simulation by breaking the constraints within a cluster."]}], "indent": 4, "text": ["Group Constraints"], "extent": [880, 903], "container": true, "type": "dt"}], "container": true, "type": "dt_group"}], "indent": 0, "text": ["Cluster Type"], "role": "item", "attrs": {"id": "clustertype"}, "extent": [541, 556], "container": true, "type": "parameters_item"}, {"body": [{"indent": 4, "type": "para", "extent": [1426, 1487], "text": ["The prefix applied to the name of each clustered piece."]}], "indent": 0, "text": ["Cluster Name Prefix"], "role": "item", "extent": [1405, 1426], "container": true, "type": "parameters_item"}, {"body": [{"indent": 4, "type": "para", "extent": [1510, 1646], "text": ["Fuses together each cluster\u2019s pieces according to the ", {"text": ["Distance"], "type": "ui"}, " threshold, and removes the interior faces between those pieces."]}], "indent": 0, "text": ["Fuse Clustered Pieces"], "role": "item", "extent": [1487, 1510], "container": true, "type": "parameters_item"}, {"body": [{"indent": 4, "type": "para", "extent": [1662, 1797], "text": ["A group containing the interior polygons of the fractured geometry (e.g. the ", {"text": ["Interior Group"], "type": "ui"}, " from ", {"text": "", "fullpath": "/nodes/sop/voronoifracture", "scheme": "Node", "type": "link", "value": "/nodes/sop/voronoifracture"}, ")."]}], "indent": 0, "text": ["Interior Group"], "role": "item", "extent": [1646, 1662], "container": true, "type": "parameters_item"}, {"body": [{"indent": 4, "type": "para", "extent": [1812, 1863], "text": ["The maximum distance to fuse points together."]}], "indent": 0, "text": ["Snap Distance"], "role": "item", "extent": [1797, 1812], "container": true, "type": "parameters_item"}, {"body": [{"indent": 4, "type": "para", "extent": [1896, 2074], "text": ["After fusing, dissolves exterior edges that are shared by primitives from different source pieces.\n    This can be useful for removing fracture lines from clustered pieces."]}], "indent": 0, "text": ["Dissolve Exterior Cluster Edges"], "role": "item", "extent": [1863, 1896], "container": true, "type": "parameters_item"}, {"body": [{"indent": 4, "type": "para", "extent": [2094, 2180], "text": ["The name of the group containing constraints between pieces in the same cluster."]}], "indent": 0, "text": ["Intracluster Group"], "role": "item", "extent": [2074, 2094], "container": true, "type": "parameters_item"}, {"body": [{"indent": 4, "type": "para", "extent": [2206, 2294], "text": ["The name of the group containing constraints between pieces in different clusters."]}], "indent": 0, "text": ["Cluster to Cluster Group"], "role": "item", "extent": [2180, 2206], "container": true, "type": "parameters_item"}, {"body": [{"indent": 4, "type": "para", "extent": [2318, 2432], "text": ["The name of the group containing constraints between a piece that is in a cluster and a non-clustered piece."]}], "indent": 0, "text": ["Cluster to Piece Group"], "role": "item", "extent": [2294, 2318], "container": true, "type": "parameters_item"}, {"body": [{"indent": 4, "type": "para", "extent": [2454, 2534], "text": ["The name of the group containing constraints between non-clustered pieces."]}], "indent": 0, "text": ["Piece to Piece Group"], "role": "item", "extent": [2432, 2454], "container": true, "type": "parameters_item"}, {"body": [{"indent": 4, "type": "para", "extent": [2553, 2631], "text": ["The name of an integer point attribute on the input constraint geometry."]}], "indent": 0, "text": ["Cluster Attribute"], "role": "item", "extent": [2534, 2553], "container": true, "type": "parameters_item"}, {"body": [{"indent": 4, "type": "para", "extent": [2646, 2855], "text": ["Adds cellular noise to the input points of the constraint geometry.\n    The default behavior is to preserve the existing values of the ", {"text": ["Cluster Attribute"], "type": "ui"}, " if it exists on the input constraint geometry."]}], "indent": 0, "text": ["Cluster Noise"], "role": "item", "extent": [2631, 2646], "container": true, "type": "parameters_item"}, {"body": [{"indent": 4, "type": "para", "extent": [2879, 2944], "text": ["The offset of the cellular noise added to the input points."]}], "indent": 0, "text": ["Offset"], "role": "item", "attrs": {"id": "offset"}, "extent": [2855, 2863], "container": true, "type": "parameters_item"}, {"body": [{"indent": 4, "type": "para", "extent": [2968, 3033], "text": ["The jitter of the cellular noise added to the input points."]}], "indent": 0, "text": ["Jitter"], "role": "item", "attrs": {"id": "jitter"}, "extent": [2944, 2952], "container": true, "type": "parameters_item"}, {"body": [{"indent": 4, "type": "para", "extent": [3053, 3179], "text": ["The size of the cells for the noise added to the input points.\n    This roughly corresponds to the size of the clusters."]}], "indent": 0, "text": ["Size"], "role": "item", "attrs": {"id": "size"}, "extent": [3033, 3039], "container": true, "type": "parameters_item"}, {"body": [{"indent": 4, "type": "para", "extent": [3220, 3263], "text": ["Randomly detach pieces from clusters."]}], "indent": 0, "text": ["Random Detachment"], "role": "item", "attrs": {"id": "randomdetach"}, "extent": [3179, 3198], "container": true, "type": "parameters_item"}, {"body": [{"indent": 4, "type": "para", "extent": [3296, 3338], "text": ["The random seed used for detachment."]}], "indent": 0, "text": ["Detach Seed"], "role": "item", "attrs": {"id": "detachseed"}, "extent": [3263, 3276], "container": true, "type": "parameters_item"}, {"body": [{"indent": 4, "type": "para", "extent": [3373, 3436], "text": ["The probability that a particular piece will be detached."]}], "indent": 0, "text": ["Detach Ratio"], "role": "item", "attrs": {"id": "detachratio"}, "extent": [3338, 3352], "container": true, "type": "parameters_item"}], "container": true, "role": "item_group", "type": "parameters_item_group"}], "indent": 0, "level": 1, "text": "Parameters", "role": "section", "extent": [529, 541], "container": true, "type": "parameters_section", "id": "parameters"}, {"body": [{"body": [{"indent": 4, "blevel": 6, "type": "bullet", "extent": [3445, 3478], "text": [{"text": "", "fullpath": "/nodes/sop/booleanfracture", "scheme": "Node", "type": "link", "value": "/nodes/sop/booleanfracture"}]}, {"indent": 4, "blevel": 6, "type": "bullet", "extent": [3478, 3513], "text": [{"text": "", "fullpath": "/nodes/sop/rbdinteriordetail", "scheme": "Node", "type": "link", "value": "/nodes/sop/rbdinteriordetail"}]}, {"indent": 4, "blevel": 6, "type": "bullet", "extent": [3513, 3546], "text": [{"text": "", "fullpath": "/nodes/sop/voronoifracture", "scheme": "Node", "type": "link", "value": "/nodes/sop/voronoifracture"}]}], "container": true, "type": "bullet_group"}], "indent": 0, "level": 1, "text": "Related", "role": "section", "extent": [3436, 3445], "container": true, "type": "related_section", "id": "related"}], "summary": ["Combines fractured pieces or constraints into larger clusters."], "type": "root", "attrs": {"version": "2.0", "tags": "break", "since": "18.0", "namespace": null, "internal": "rbdcluster::2.0", "context": "sop", "type": "node", "icon": "SOP/rbdcluster"}, "title": ["RBD Cluster"]}